==English==

===Etymology===
From mediaeval Latin or archaic French ''alcohol'' (modern French [[alcool]]), from Arabic {{ARchar|[[كحل|الكحل]]}} (al-kuħl) ‘[[kohl]]’.

===Noun===
'''alcohol'''
# An [[intoxicating]] beverage made by the [[fermentation]] of [[sugar]] or sugar-containing material.
# {{chemistry}} Any of a [[class]] of [[organic]] [[compounds]] (such as [[ethanol]]) containing a [[hydroxyl]] [[functional group]](-OH).

====Related terms====
*[[alcoholic]]
*[[alcoholism]]
*[[low-alcohol]]
*[[non-alcoholic]]
*[[nonalcoholic]]

